The paper discusses the use of MCTS, a search procedure commonly used in AI, to simplify expressions in high energy physics. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions common subexpression elimination, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of Horner schemes and performance analysis suggest the sub-category of computer engineering (cs.CE). The paper also deals with numerical integration, which is a topic in scientific computing (cs.SC). Finally, the mention of exploration-exploitation trade-offs suggests the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
